The paper focuses on data compression techniques for mini-batch stochastic gradient descent, which is a popular algorithm in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses matrix operations and data access patterns, which are relevant to categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper uses real-world datasets, which could fall under categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
